Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is light-brown in section and contains a number of small metallic inclusions, the exterior is covered with a red-brown slip and very smudged remains of three lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393793) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393793)
